TY  - JOUR
AU  - Segura, Anatoli
T1  - Why Did Sponsor Banks Rescue Their SIVs? A Signaling Model of Rescues*
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfx024
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 22
IS  - 2
SP  - 661
EP  - 697
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - At the beginning of the past financial crisis sponsoring banks rescued their structured investment vehicles (SIVs) despite of lack of contractual obligation to do so. I show that this outcome may arise as the equilibrium of a signaling game between banks and their debt investors when a negative shock affects the correlated asset returns of a fraction of banks and their sponsored vehicles. The rescue is interpreted as a good signal and reduces the refinancing costs of the sponsoring bank. If banks’ leverage is high or the negative shock is sizable enough, the equilibrium is a pooling one in which all banks rescue. When the aggregate financial sector is close to insolvency, banks’ expected net worth would increase if rescues were banned. The model can be extended to discuss the circumstances in which all banks collapse after rescuing their vehicles.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfx024
ER  - 



